Overview

This event will be a collegiate cross country event with distances of 5K for women and 8K for men. Participation will include up to 12 NAIA/Mid-South Conference member-institutions from Kentucky, Southern Ohio and Tennessee. We anticipate fields of 90-120 runners per gender. All athletes will be preregistered before the event with no opportunity for walk-up registration. Teams will be assigned their own tent area and only coaches and athletes will be allowed in assigned team areas. Portable toilets and hand washing /hand sanitizer stations will be available for all athletes in the team area. Athletes and Coaches will be expected to wear masks at all times on race day, except when warming up, cooling down and racing.

Environment

  • Event will take place at Phil Moore Park Bowling Green, KY.
  • No spectators will be allowed for this event.
  • Attendance will include athletes, coaches and support staff only.
  • Signs will be posted, reminding all present, to remain six feet apart, wear masks, and not touch face.
  • Athletic Trainers will be on duty to take temperatures and symptom check all participants upon arrival atthe course on race day.

Volunteer training

Volunteers will be trained in event protocol prior to event. Temperature checks will be conducted for all volunteers. Masks and gloves will be worn at all times.

Safety Protocols

Athletes/Coaches

  • All athletes/teams will pre-register. No day of race registration. This will allow for a limited number of people at the park and help assure that safety protocols are followed and manageable.
  • Athletic Trainers, coaches and/or other approved symptom checkers will do temperature checks/Covid19 questionnaires for their own athletes prior to entering the team area. Athletes will not be admitted before arrival of coach and temp checks. Coaches will be instructed to enter with their teams as a group.
  • Athletes and Coaches will wear masks upon arrival at the park. No team member will be allowed to enter the athlete section without a mask.
  • Teams will be assigned an area to wait for their race event. Each team is responsible for bringing their own tent. Each team area will be sectioned off from other teams. Athletes may take off masks for warmup and must put them back on until called to the start line. Coaches will be positioned at the start-line to collect their athletes’ masks just prior to the start.
  • Each team starting box will be marked 6 feet apart. Only participating athletes/coaches and race starter will be allowed in start area.
  • When athletes cross the finish line, they will walk out of the finish area and return to their assigned team area. They will remain there until all teammates are finished and then will be allowed to cool down as a team. After cool-down, teams will remain in the assigned team area until the conclusion of both races. Masks will be required when leaving the team area and upon exiting the facility.
  • Teams will be responsible for bring their own water, snacks etc. No food or beverages (including community water stations) will be provided on race day.

Volunteers/Race Staff

  • Volunteers/race staff will wear gloves and masks at all times.
  • Volunteers/race staff will be socially distanced whenever feasible.
  • Volunteers will help direct teams to respective areas whenever applicable.

Spectators

  • No spectators will be allowed in the race area on race day.

Awards

  • No award ceremony
  • Any awards will be mailed to the coaches after the event.

Results

  • A copy of the race results will be given to each head coach.
  • No results will be posted for participant viewing.

Concessions

  • No concessions or T-shirt sales.

Disinfecting/Sanitizing

  • Each team will be instructed and expected to provide their own hand sanitizer. Hand washing/sanitizer stations will be provided for general use in the team areas and at the finish line area.
  • Athletes, coaches and support staff will be instructed and expected to bring their own masks and gloves and will be required to wear masks at all times except as previously noted.
  • Race organizer will have athletic trainers on site to make sure that all teams/participants are following protocols

Additional Notes

  • Anyone who does not follow social distancing rules or does not wear a mask will be asked to either comply or leave the park. If they do not comply, they will be given 10 minutes and then security will be called. We reserve the right to disqualify any athlete or team who does not follow the guidelines set forth.

Race Schedule

  • Men’s 8K race will begin at 1:30pm Central Time
  • Women’s 5K race will begin at 2:30pm Central Time
